The paper focuses on reinforcement learning for robotics, specifically for multi-step visual tasks. This suggests that it is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reward functions and the efficiency of the learning algorithm, which are common topics in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of visual input for the tasks suggests that Computer Vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the ability to transfer the learned model from simulation to the real world, which suggests that the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may also be relevant.
